$ Avaloq: PL/SQL package session#
@ session#

Executing `session#.open_session` is needed to be able to query the → Companies-Products/Avaloq/development/tables/obj[`obj`] and
→ Companies-Products/Avaloq/development/tables/doc[`doc`] tables.

code {
begin
  session#.open_session;
end;
/
code }

Opening with a default business unit:
code {
begin
  session#.open_session(
    i_bu_id => nvl(
                 base_par#.base_par#id('avg.bgp_param', 'dflt_bu_id'),
                 0
              )
  );
end;
/
code }

Opening a sessin with `i_bu_id => -1` apparently opens a session in the so called sentinel:

sa:
 The → Companies-Products/Avaloq/development/DDIC/session → Companies-Products/Avaloq/development/DDIC.
